API

https://nem.raywalker.it/api/v1.0/scada

time_start or start_time
Generation results from this date. Any standard timestring or unix timestamp is accepted
time_end or end_time
Generation results up to and including this date. And standard timestring or unix timestamp is accepted
days or weeks or months or hours
Show results from this interval. If used with time_start, then it will show results from that date to the future, if used with time_end it will show days preceeding that date
Examples include:
  • ?days=7&time_start=2014-12-20
    Retrieve all values for 7 days from the 20th December 2014
  • ?hours=1&end_time=2014-03-01T11:00Z
    All results from 1st March 2014, 11am UTC
